Another nice thing about this, is how simple it is to switch from stateless to stateful, for example, if you have a very large widget, and are sick of calling `useRef`, you could switch over the above very easily:
```
(+4 lines ^)
class _MyViewState extends State<MyView> with StatefulPropsMixin {
  MyView(this.duration);
  final Duration duration;

  BoolProp _bool1;
  AnimatorControllerProp _anim1;

  @override
  void initProps(){
    _bool1 = addProp(false);
    _anim1 = syncProp((c, w) => AnimatorControllerProp(
        duration: w.duration, vsync: c.read<TickerProvider>())); //Notice the external deps, no need for didChange diff
  }

 @override
  void buildWithProps(){
      // Setting `_bool1.value = true` would rebuild the view  automatically, 
      // Set to `false` (currentValue), and rebuild is skipped, prop optimizes internally
    return FadeTransition(opacity: _anim1.controller, child: Text("${_bool1.value}"));
  }
}
```

