Here is something different, similiar to reactives (super confusing name btw), but from a different angle:

```dart
class _PageViewState extends State<PageView> with HostMixin {
  // createComponent is a generic method provided by HostMixin
  // that will allow us to create the Paginator and configure stuff around it
  late final _paginator = createComponent(Paginator(), (x) {
    // x is of type AttachedComponent<Paginator, PageView>
    // you can easily add extension to this class for your own helpers

    // this closure will be called once, just before _paginator has been set
    // to allow us a chance of configuring what we want to configure

    // we can't use _paginator here because it's not initialized yet
    // but Dart is kind enough to give us an error (sadly, only when infering the type)

    // if widget.page changed, call setPage on paginator
    x.onWidgetUpdate((widget) => widget.page, x.instance.setPage);

    // if Paginator is Listenable, call setState on every change
    x.setStateOnChange();
  });

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Text("${_paginator.data}");
  }
}
```
Basically you can use `createComponent` method to specify how paginator in this example interacts with widget and with state.

The core of this approach is `x` declared in closure, which has various methods for adding callbacks into State methods, that HostMixin will ensure to call.

